Nairobi, Kenya: Power blackout has hit Nairobi, Coast and Mt Kenya regions following a technical fault at Ndenderu substation. Kenya Power says a technical fault at Ndenderu sub-station is to blame for the power outage.The technical fault occurred this morning cutting off supplies from Olkaria geothermal fields to the City.&nbsp;The Company&rsquo;s General Manager for Network Management, Eng. Daniel Tare, said the technical teams are on the ground to restore power supply as quickly as possible. &ldquo;We regret any inconvenience caused by the outage,&rdquo; Eng. Tare said. ALSO READ: Ben Chumo bows out as Kenya Power names Ken Tarus acting CEO